==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ro-setta stone
<hw>Ro-set"ta stone`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A stone found at
<xex>Rosetta</xex>, in Egypt, bearing a trilingual inscription, by aid
of which, with other inscriptions, a key was obtained to the
hieroglyphics of ancient Egypt.</def> <rj><au>Brande & C.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rosetta wood</ent>⟦br⟧
